author: Arman Liew
title: 10-Minute Cauliflower Fried Rice - The Big Man's World \u00ae
text:
Skip the carbs, but keep the flavor with this easy cauliflower fried rice recipe. Ready in 10 minutes and easy to customize!
Love creative cauliflower recipes? Try my cauliflower pizza crust , cauliflower mashed potatoes , and air fryer buffalo cauliflower .
Cauliflower has been a lifesaver when it comes to keto recipes, especially this homemade cauliflower rice.
With all of the flavor of traditional fried rice but a fraction of the carbs, it‚Äôs a low-carb substitution that doesn‚Äôt make me feel like I have to sacrifice.
Table of Contents Why I love this recipe Ingredients needed How to make cauliflower fried rice Arman‚Äôs recipe tips and variations Storage instructions More creative cauliflower recipes Cauliflower Fried Rice (Recipe Card) Why I love this recipe A creative take on cauliflower. Like cauliflower steak and air fryer cauliflower , this is no simple steamed side dish. It‚Äôs cauliflower at its finest! Makes great leftovers. Just like regular fried rice, this recipe reheats like magic and tastes even better the next day. Low-carb and low-calorie. A single serving of this cauliflower rice has just 8 grams of net carbs and under 200 calories, compared to traditional fried rice, which has over 40 grams of carbs for nearly double the calories! Easy to customize. You can add whatever vegetables, seasonings, or protein you desire. I‚Äôll be sure to give you plenty of suggestions later on. Ingredients needed Cauliflower. Grate the florets in a rice-like texture, process them in a food processor, or get pre-riced cauliflower from the store. If you‚Äôre using frozen cauliflower rice, let it thaw overnight or microwave it for 30 seconds, then remove the excess moisture with paper towels before cooking. Olive oil. You can substitute it with any other neutral-flavored oil. Vegetables. My favorites are onions, carrots, red bell peppers, and frozen peas. Fresh ginger and garlic. Essentials for any good fried rice recipe. I highly recommend buying them fresh. Salt. To taste. Soy sauce. Another fried rice essential. Use gluten-free tamari if needed. Sesame oil. Optional. Feel free to skip it if you don‚Äôt like it, or use lightly toasted sesame oil for a more subtle sesame flavor. Large eggs. Preferably room-temperature and freshly whisked. How to make cauliflower fried rice I‚Äôve included step-by-step photos below to make this recipe easy to follow at home. For the full printable recipe instructions and ingredient quantities, scroll to the recipe card at the bottom of this post.
Step 1- Make the cauliflower rice. In a high-speed blender or food processor, add the chopped cauliflower florets and pulse until it reaches a rice-like consistency.
Step 2- Cook the veggies. In a large wok or skillet over medium heat, add the oil. Once hot, add the garlic and ginger and fry for 1-2 minutes, then add the carrots, peppers, peas, onions, and riced cauliflower. Cook for 3-4 minutes or until the veggies are softened.
Step 3- Cook eggs. Push the veggies to one side, add the sesame oil, then add the eggs and gently scramble them. Combine them with the veggies.
Step 4- Add soy sauce. Add the soy sauce and stir fry for 1-2 minutes before removing the pan from the heat and serving warm.
Arman‚Äôs recipe tips and variations Use a large skillet. So that the rice gets equal access to the heat and gets a subtle fried exterior. To avoid soggy cauliflower rice , don‚Äôt over-cook it. The longer it cooks, the more water is released. Chop the veggies evenly. So they cook at the same time. Add protein. To make a heartier dish, I like to add chopped chicken breast, sauteed shrimp , or beef. Make vegan fried rice. Skip the egg and add crispy baked tofu . Garnish. While optional, I like to add toasted sesame seeds and chopped green onions for extra flavor and a pop of color. Make kimchi fried rice. Add ½ cup of drained and chopped kimchi to the skillet right before serving. Storage instructions To store: Leftovers can be stored in the refrigerator in airtight containers for up to 3 days.
To freeze: Place the cooked cauliflower fried rice in a container to freeze for 2-3 months. Let it thaw overnight in the fridge, or add more reheating time.
To reheat: Leftover fried rice should be reheated in the microwave or in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until warm.

Servings: 4 servings Prep: 1 minute min Cook: 9 minutes mins Total: 10 minutes mins Rate This Recipe Pin Print Ingredients 1x 2x 3x ‚ñ¢ 1 large cauliflower ‚ñ¢ 1 tablespoon oil ‚ñ¢ 2 cloves garlic chopped finely ‚ñ¢ 1 large onion chopped finely ‚ñ¢ 1 teaspoon ginger spring onions ‚ñ¢ 1/4 cup carrots chopped finely ‚ñ¢ 1/2 large bell pepper chopped ‚ñ¢ 1 cup frozen peas ‚ñ¢ 1 tablespoon sesame oil ‚ñ¢ 2 large eggs whisked ‚ñ¢ 1/4 cup soy sauce Instructions In a high speed blender or food processor, add your chopped cauliflower and pulse until a rice-like consistency. Set aside. In a large wok or frying pan, add your oil and place over medium heat. Once hot, add your onions and garlic and fry for 1-2 minutes, before adding your carrots, peppers, frozen peas, and riced cauliflower and cook for 3-4 minutes, until softened. Push the vegetables to one side and add the sesame oil then add the eggs and gently scramble them. Mix them through the vegetables. Add the soy sauce stir fry for 1-2 minutes, before removing the pan off the heat. Notes TO STORE : Leftovers can be stored in the refrigerator in air-tight containers for up to 3 days. TO FREEZE : Place the cooked cauliflower fried rice in a container to freeze for 2-3 months. TO REHEAT : Always reheat the rice in a non-stick pan until hot. author: Vaishali Shastri
title: Tamil Nadu Rains: Severe waterlogging in these regions; IMD predicts heavy rainfall predicted in multiple
text:
Source: DNA | Title: Tamil Nadu Rains: Severe waterlogging in these regions; IMD predicts heavy rainfall predicted in multiple districts
The India Meteorological Department (IMD) on Friday issued a warning for Tamil Nadu, forecasting heavy rainfall across multiple districts until December 14.
The India Meteorological Department (IMD) on Friday issued a warning for Tamil Nadu, forecasting heavy rainfall across multiple districts until December 14. Severe waterlogging was reported in Trichy following incessant rain, while Thoothukudi and other districts experienced moderate to heavy rainfall.
The IMD predicts moderate thunderstorms with heavy rain in districts like Ariyalur, and Perambalur. Thiruchirapalli, Karur, Dindigul, Mayiladuthurai, Nagapattinam, Thanjavur, Thiruvarur, Tenkasi, Theni, Virudhunagar, Pudukkottai Ramanathapuram and Sivaganga districts of Tamilnadu and Karaikal area.
The resultant weather conditions could lead to water logging and the traffic may be affected in some areas.
Light Thunderstorms & lightning with Light to Moderate rain are very likely at one or two places over Cuddalore, Salem, Namakkal, Nilgiris, and Coimbatore. Tiruppur, Tirunelveli and Thoothukkudi districts of Tamilnadu. The Thiruvallur and Chengalpattu districts of Tamilnadu will receive light rain.
Tamil Nadu‚Äôs weather forecast predicted a maximum temperature of 28-29¬∞C, and a minimum temperature of 24-25¬∞C, with partly cloudy skies and a chance of light to moderate rain within the next 24 hours in several districts.
Meanwhile, IMD has also predicted heavy to very heavy rainfall likely at isolated places over other southern parts of India, mainly in Karaikal, Lakshadweep, and Andaman and Nicobar Islands.
According to IMD, the well-marked low-pressure area that was previously located over the Gulf of Mannar and nearby regions has now shifted to a low-pressure zone over the Gulf of Mannar and the adjacent Comorin area.
As per the update, the system‚Äôs upper air cyclonic circulation extends up to mid-tropospheric levels. It is expected to move westward towards the Maldives and the nearby Lakshadweep area, crossing the Comorin region. The system is anticipated to weaken gradually over the next 24 hours, with a diminishing impact on the surrounding areas.
(Except for the headline, this story has not been edited by DNA staff and is published from ANI)

text: Tras la lesi√≥n de CJ Dos Santos, suplente de Drake Callender, el arquero argentino de 38 a√±os Oscar Ustari se suma al Inter Miami en condici√≥n de futbolista libre tras su paso por el Audax Italiano de Chile. Fue campe√≥n con Leo Messi de la Copa del Mundo Sub-20 disputada en Pa√≠ses Bajos en 2005 y de los Juegos Ol√≠mpicos de Beijing 2008. Ustari, surgido en Independiente, tuvo pasos por Boca Juniors (Argentina), Getafe y Almer√≠a (Liga Espa√±ola), Sunderland (Premier League) y Pachuca (LIGA MX), donde jug√≥ entre 2020 y 2023. Se encontraba sin club tras su breve paso por Audax Italiano. Llega para reemplazar al arquero suplente del equipo del sur de la Florida, CJ Dos Santos quien "ser√° sometido a una cirug√≠a para reparar un hueso roto en su mano izquierda, y su tiempo de recuperaci√≥n tras el procedimiento determinar√° cu√°ndo podr√° regresar a los terrenos de juego", comunic√≥ el club el pasado 30 de agosto. Ustari ha compartido campo de juego con Leo Messi en el ya mencionado Mundial Juvenil Sub-20 y en los Juegos Ol√≠mpicos de Beijing 2008, donde Argentina se coron√≥ campe√≥n en ambos cert√°menes. Tambi√©n estuvieron juntos en el plantel de la Copa del Mundo de Alemania 2006. Desde entonces, han cultivado una s√≥lida amistad y recientemente se les ha visto juntos en varios eventos en Miami, acompa√±ados por el Kun Ag√ºero y Maxi Rodr√≠guez. Seg√∫n trascendidos, el arquero ya se entrena junto a sus nuevos compa√±eros en el Florida Training Center de Fort Lauderdale y su vinculo con el l√≠der del Supporters' Shield y de la Conferencia Este ser√≠a hasta el final de la temporada. La gloria en la Liga MX con los Tuzos A Pachuca lleg√≥ en enero del 2020 y al poco tiempo se gan√≥ un lugar en el equipo titular por su buen rendimiento bajo los tres palos. En 2022 se consagr√≥ campe√≥n del Apertura de la Liga MX, siendo titular indiscutido. Las lesiones que marcaron su carrera Ustari estaba llamado a ser uno de los grandes arqueros de la Selecci√≥n Argentina, pero se rompi√≥ dos veces los ligamentos cruzados, una vez el tend√≥n rotuliano, se fractur√≥ el brazo y la mand√≠bula. Esas lesiones lo marginaron por una gran cantidad de d√≠as de los campos de juegos. title: Tinder lanza advertencia a sus usuarios: Modus operandi de las ‚Äògoteras‚Äô llega a Colombia ‚Äì El Financiero
text: [Tinder](https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/mundo/2022/09/29/cae-el-galan-de-tinder-el-brasileno-que-estafaba-a-mujeres-asi-era-su-modus-operandi/) emiti√≥ una advertencia de seguridad a sus usuarios en [Colombia ](https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/mundo/2024/01/13/video-derrumbe-en-colombia-deja-33-fallecidos-en-carretera-de-choco/)debido a un aumento en el n√∫mero de delincuentes que utilizan la popular aplicaci√≥n de citas para atraer a las v√≠ctimas a las que drogan y roban. ‚ÄúRecientemente, ha habido advertencias gubernamentales sobre mayores riesgos en ciertas regiones‚Äù, seg√∫n un mensaje en la aplicaci√≥n enviado a los usuarios de Tinder. ‚ÄúRecuerde examinar sus partidos, reunirse en lugares p√∫blicos y compartir planes con personas en las que conf√≠e. Si algo se siente mal, puedes terminar la cita‚Äù. Tinder warning its users to be more careful.‚Äî Medell√≠n Unmapped üá®üá¥ (@MedellinEchoes) ‚ÄúFollow your instincts‚Äù lol. Yeah, that has worked really well here in Medell√≠nüòÖ [pic.twitter.com/e3ikPAug4b] [January 24, 2024] Un portavoz de Match Group Inc, la empresa matriz de la aplicaci√≥n de citas m√°s grande, confirm√≥ el contenido del mensaje, que fue enviado a los usuarios a partir del mi√©rcoles. El portavoz tambi√©n dijo que Tinder se ha comprometido con funcionarios locales que han estado investigando delitos relacionados con extranjeros y ‚Äúapoyar√° plenamente con cualquier informaci√≥n que les sea √∫til‚Äù, sin indicar qu√© funcionarios pueden haber solicitado. La Embajada de Estados Unidos en Bogot√° advirti√≥ a los estadounidenses a principios de este mes sobre los riesgos del uso de aplicaciones de citas en l√≠nea en la regi√≥n, luego de un aumento de la actividad criminal en las principales ciudades colombianas, donde los delincuentes las usaban para reunirse con extranjeros en lugares p√∫blicos, y luego drogarlos, agredirlos y robarles. Entre el 1 de noviembre y el 31 de diciembre del a√±o pasado, ocho ciudadanos estadounidenses murieron en Medell√≠n, seg√∫n la embajada, que dijo que las muertes fueron el resultado de una presunta sobredosis involuntaria de drogas o un presunto homicidio. Durante el √∫ltimo a√±o, la embajada dijo que ha visto un aumento de incidentes relacionados con aplicaciones de citas en l√≠nea que se utilizan para atraer a las v√≠ctimas, generalmente extranjeras, para robar por la fuerza o, a veces, usar sedantes para drogarlas primero. Este tipo de delitos ‚Äúrutinariamente no se denuncian, ya que las v√≠ctimas se sienten avergonzadas y no quieren seguir adelante con el proceso judicial‚Äù, dijo la embajada. Despu√©s de la pandemia, [Medell√≠n](https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/mis-finanzas/2023/03/11/una-casita-en-colombia-con-el-superpeso-puedes-comprar-una-casa-en-medellin/), la segunda ciudad m√°s grande de Colombia, recibi√≥ casi 1.4 millones de visitantes del exterior en 2022, superando por primera vez a Cartagena. El alcalde de Medell√≠n, Federico Guti√©rrez, dijo a principios de este mes que la ciudad quiere impulsar el turismo, pero advirti√≥ a los viajeros contra las pr√°cticas relacionadas con el consumo de drogas y la explotaci√≥n sexual. ‚ÄúSigan sus instintos‚Äù, dijo Tinder a sus usuarios en Colombia.
